about.summary: Split an iterable into multiple using arbitrary predicates.

name: multisplitby
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "multisplitby" %}
{% set version = "0.0.1" %}
{% set sha256 = "e40489fa174fd7afd28a895477e6eefc64d6cfd863cca6900530e436a40e356f" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.5
  run:
    - python >=3.5
    
test:
  imports:
    - multisplitby

about:
  home: https://github.com/cthoyt/multisplitby
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: "Split an iterable into multiple using arbitrary predicates."

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - npavlovikj
